Got it üëç Here‚Äôs a sample Objectives and Benefits section you can use in your proposal:


---

Objectives

Automate the coefficient value input process into SAP using WinActor.

Ensure accuracy and consistency of data entry by eliminating manual errors.

Standardize the coefficient value template for easier processing.

Generate a prooflist (via screenshots) to provide evidence of successful updates.

Send automated email notifications to stakeholders after every update.

Reduce operation time and free up manpower for higher-value tasks.



---

Benefits

Accuracy: Minimizes human errors during SAP data entry.

Efficiency: Speeds up processing time compared to manual input.

Traceability: Prooflist screenshots serve as evidence for audit and verification.

Transparency: Automated email notifications keep all stakeholders informed.

Consistency: Standardized template ensures uniform data handling.

Cost Savings: Reduces overtime and manual rework caused by entry mistakes.

Scalability: RPA workflow can be expanded to other SAP processes in the future.



